                <div>
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Lakes &mdash;</h3>
                    Elbow River is just west of the neighbourhood. As a resident of Bel-Aire, you will have direct access to the Elbow River’s pathway, where you can enjoy long walks and runs.
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Golf &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Bel-Aire’s golf lovers have access to various golf courses, but some of the best golf courses are only a stone’s throw away from the neighbourhood.</p>
                    <p>Calgary Golf and Country Club is a private golf club located immediately north of Bel-Air. The club is Alberta’s oldest golf club and boasts lush greens, spectacular landscaping, and a fantastic golfing experience.</p>
                    <p>Earl Grey Golf Course is another of Calgary’s premier private golf clubs, providing its members with a world-class golf experience and social experience. Located close to the Glenmore Reservoir, Earl Grey Golf Course offers its members fantastic views and landscapes and a very inviting atmosphere.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Bel-Aire’s younger children have access to modern playgrounds with the latest outdoor playground equipment. They also have access to neighbouring playgrounds like Medford Pl SW Playground. Meadowview Park has a playground for younger children and a ball diamond for older children and families.</p>
                    <p>Elbow River – Calgary’s second-largest river flows from the Rockies through the city and is a stone’s throw away from Bel-Aire. A 5.4-mile pathway along the river makes for a splendid walk. The River is a fantastic picnic spot and popular among hikers.</p>
                    <p>Glenmore Reservoir is another fantastic area with a 15.4 km walking trail that loop around it. The loop trail is a multi-use path that hikers, walkers, and bikers enjoy.</p>
                    <p>Glenmore Dam Off-Leash Dog Park is a fantastic area to allow your dogs some time off their leash.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div>
            <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Shopping &mdash;</h3>
                <p>Bel-Aire’s avid shoppers head toward CF Chinook Shopping Center (a four-minute drive) for a luxurious shopping experience. CF Chinook on Macleod Trail is a sophisticated shopping complex with over 250 high-end stores, entertainment, and restaurants.</p>
                <p>Britannia Plaza Shopping Centre is also a four-minute drive north of Bel-Aire. BP is a quaint little collection of street-side shops with a small-town feel. The shops offer fashion items, gift items, books, home accessories, and grocery and food services. The plaza also has higher-end services like a 5-star chocolate store and a fresh food market called Sunterra.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Fitness &mdash;</h3>
                <p>For Pilates, the Calgary Pilates Center on Elbow Drive is a little over a kilometer from Bel-Aire. The Bel-Aire Mayfair Pathway Art Project and Gym is a full-fledged gym within the community.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Restaurants and bars &mdash;</h3>
                <p>While there are no restaurants and bars within the community, residents of Bel-Aire have a variety of restaurants to try in CF Chinook Shopping Center. Some of these are:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>JOEY Chinook for international and regional dishes</li>
                    <li>Hula Chinook for fast food</li>
                    <li>Buffo Ristorante for Italian</li>
                    <li>Globefish for sushi</li>
                </ul>
                <p>There are several pizzerias in the center for pizza lovers.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
