                <p>Heritage Park Historical Village is a 127-acre historical park and only a seven-minute drive from Bel-Aire. This is the country’s second-largest living history museum and one of Calgary’s most visited tourist destinations. The park boasts over 55,000 artifacts, over 180 exhibits, various shows, and a chance to learn about the history and cultural traditions of the land on which the park stands.</p>
